%N A397377 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(2) - H(k,2))*H(2*k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397377 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.31, p. 432, eq. (4.122), section 5.31, p. 463, section 6.31, pp. 657-661.
%H A397377 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397377 Equals log(2)^4/4 - 57*zeta(4)/16 + 7*log(2)*zeta(3)/2 - 3*log(2)^2*zeta(2)/2 + 6*Li_4(1/2).
%e A397377 1.037544565964227437581453082201714420302904256757042...
